<item>
            <title>[SOLR-13453] JWTAuthPluginIntegrationTest and TestSolrCloudWithHadoopAuthPlugin get failed when SolrClientNodeStateProvider behave nicely</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-13453</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-13449&quot; title=&quot;SolrClientNodeStateProvider always retries on requesting metrics from other nodes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-13449&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-13449&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is a trivial fix for SolrClientNodeStateProvider, it makes the provider stop retry once the metrics are successfully grabbed. &lt;br/&gt;
In an unexpected way, JWTAuthPluginIntegrationTest and TestSolrCloudWithHadoopAuthPlugin get failed 100%. This is bugs of tests for sure.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
